5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to higher education; to add Chapter 5B to
10 Title 16, Code of Alabama 1975, commencing with Section
11 16-5B-1; to create the College and Higher Education Excellence
12 and Results (CHEER) Act; to establish a process to provide
13 bonus funding to higher education institutions that meet
14 identified student and institution performance goals and
15 objectives; to establish the College and Higher Education
16 Excellence and Results (CHEER) Fund and provide for its
17 funding and appropriations; and to establish the
18 Outcomes-Based Higher Education Funding Coordinating Committee
19 and provide for its duties and responsibilities.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. Chapter 5B is added to Title 16, Code of
22 Alabama 1975, commencing with Section 16-5B-1, to read as
23 follows:
24 §16-5B-1
25 This act shall be known and may be cited as the College
26 and Higher Education Excellence and Results (CHEER) Act.
27 §16-5B-2
28 For the purposes of this chapter, the following terms
Page 1

For the purposes of this chapter, the following terms
HB565 Engrossed
29 have the following meanings:
30 (1) ACADEMICALLY UNDERPREPARED STUDENT. A student that
31 started his or her academic program without meeting the
32 readiness requirements established by the Outcomes-Based
33 Higher Education Funding Coordinating Committee in discussion
34 with the individual institutions.
35 (2) ADULT LEARNER. A student that is 25 years of age or
36 older.
37 (3) ALABAMA COMMISSION ON HIGHER EDUCATION (ACHE). The
38 commission established in Chapter 5 of Title 16, Code of
39 Alabama 1975.
40 (4) AVAILABLE FUNDING MULTIPLIER. Formula used to
41 determine the annual amount of bonus funding available to each
42 eligible institution calculated like the higher education
43 portion of the funds appropriated from the Education Trust
44 Fund Advancement and Technology Fund pursuant to Section
45 29-9-4, excluding dual enrollment students from the
46 calculation.
47 (5) BASE YEAR. The year established by the
48 Outcomes-Based Higher Education Funding Coordinating Committee
49 in discussion with the individual institutions to reflect the
50 reference point prior to the performance year to be used to
51 measure and compare performance and outcome changes over time.
52 (6) COLLEGE AND HIGHER EDUCATION EXCELLENCE AND RESULTS
53 (CHEER) FUND. The fund created by this chapter to provide
54 bonus funding to higher education institutions that meet
55 identified student and institution performance goals and
56 objectives.
