57 (7) COMMITTEE. The Outcomes-Based Higher Education
58 Funding Coordinating Committee established in Section 16-5B-6.
59 (8) COMPLETION. The number of degrees or certificates
60 awarded by an eligible institution.
61 (9) CREDIT. One semester credit hour or the equivalent.
62 (10) EDUCATIONAL PROGRAM. A program that leads to a
63 certificate, an associate degree, bachelor's degree, technical
64 degree, micro-credential, industry credential, graduate degree
65 or any other program as defined by the Outcomes-Based Higher
66 Education Funding Coordinating Committee in discussion with
67 the individual institutions.
68 (11) ELIGIBLE INSTITUTIONS. The following institutions:
69 a. Alabama A&M University.
70 b. Alabama State University.
71 c. Athens State University.
72 d. Auburn University.
73 e. Auburn University at Montgomery.
74 f. Jacksonville State University.
75 g. Troy University.
76 h. The University of Alabama at Birmingham.
77 i. The University of Alabama in Huntsville.
78 j. The University of Alabama in Tuscaloosa.
79 k. University of Montevallo.
80 l. University of North Alabama.
81 m. University of South Alabama.
82 n. University of West Alabama.
83 o. Tuskegee University.
84 p. Community and technical colleges that are part of
