85 the Alabama Community College System.
86 (12) EMPLOYED IN A HIGH-DEMAND FIELD. A graduated
87 student is employed in a job with more jobs available than
88 qualified candidates to fill or where there will be more jobs
89 available in that career over a defined period of time, as
90 determined by the Outcomes-Based Higher Education Funding
91 Coordinating Committee in discussion with the individual
92 institutions.
93 (13) EMPLOYED IN A HIGH-WAGE JOB. A graduated student
94 that is employed in a job five years after graduation with a
95 wage that is at least one of the following, for the 25 to 34
96 age group, as determined by the Outcomes-Based Higher
97 Education Funding Coordinating Committee in discussion with
98 the individual institutions:
99 a. Ten percent higher than the state median wage for
100 high school graduates, if the student passed an industry
101 credential or completed a sub-associate or technical program.
102 b. Twenty percent higher than the state median wage for
103 high school graduates, if the student earned an associate
104 degree.
105 c. Fifty percent higher than the state median wage, if
106 the student earned a bachelor's degree or other
107 post-bachelor's degree.
108 (14) ENROLLED. A student is enrolled in an educational
109 institution.
110 (15) HIGHER-NEED STUDENT. A student that is likely to
111 require additional supports and services to achieve
112 postgraduation success, including low-income students,
Page 4

postgraduation success, including low-income students,
